#: ../../reference_manual/audio_for_animation.rst:39
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Krita saves the location of your audio file. If you move the audio file "
#| "or rename it, Krita will not be able to find it. Krita will tell you the "
#| "file was moved or deleted the next time you try to open the Krita file up."
msgid ""
"Crucially, Krita only saves the location (file path) of your audio file "
"inside your Krita document. Because of that, if you happen to move or rename "
"an audio file that you've referenced in one of your Krita animations, Krita "
"will no longer be able to find it and you will need to re-load it manually. "
"However, Krita will tell you the file was moved or deleted the next time you "
"try to open the Krita file up."
msgstr ""
"Krita 會記錄音訊檔案的位置與名稱。若您移動或重命名音訊檔案，Krita 將會無法找"
"到它。在下次打開該 Krita 檔案時，Krita 會提示音訊檔案已被移動或刪除。"

#: ../../reference_manual/audio_for_animation.rst:42
msgid "Using Audio"
msgstr "使用音訊"

#: ../../reference_manual/audio_for_animation.rst:44
msgid ""
"Once you've imported some audio, you will be able scrub through frames on "
"the timeline and Krita will play the audio chunk associated with the frame "
"that you want on. Then, when you press the Play button, your audio will "
"playback while you animation plays synchronized with the image frame changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/audio_for_animation.rst:46
msgid ""
"As of now there is no visual audio waveform display in Krita's UI, so you "
"will need to use your ears and the scrubbing functionality to line your "
"keyframes up with specific parts of the audio."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/audio_for_animation.rst:50
msgid "Exporting with Audio"
msgstr "連同音訊匯出"

#: ../../reference_manual/audio_for_animation.rst:52
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "To get the audio file included when you are exporting, you need to "
#| "include it in the Render Animation options. In the :menuselection:`File --"
